# Meet the prerequisites:
#* A virtual server running Linux (e.g. Ubuntu server with IP address `xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx`)
#* A domain name (e.g. `yyy.com`)
	
# ssh to the virtual server, make sure that `host` is a sudo user. <div>

```bash
ssh host@xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx
```

</div>

# Setup the firewall. <div>

```bash
ufw allow OpenSSH
ufw enable
```

</div>

# Install Nextcloud and create a account (e.g. account `user1` with password `password123`). <div>

```bash
sudo snap install nextcloud
sudo nextcloud.manual-install user1 password123
```

</div>

# Setup the domain on the server. <div>

```bash
sudo nextcloud.occ config:system:set trusted_domains 1 --value=yyy.com
sudo ufw allow 80,443/tcp
```

</div>
	
# Setup ''Letâ€™s Encrypt'' for SSL/TLS certificates. <div>

```bash
sudo nextcloud.enable-https lets-encrypt
```

</div>
	
